# ============================================================================
# PROJECT SPECIFIC (KEEP THESE)
# ============================================================================

# Keep these files in the repository
!requirements.txt
!README.md
!QUICKSTART.md
!maintenance_plan.md
!monitoring_strategy.md
!PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md
!PROJECT_SUMMARY.md
!START_HERE.md
!.gitignore

# Keep sample data (small files only)
!sample_input.json

# Keep source code
!train_model.py
!batch_score.py
!app/main.py

# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================

# This .gitignore is configured for a Machine Learning production project
# 
# What IS committed:
# - Source code (.py files)
# - Documentation (.md files)
# - Configuration (requirements.txt)
# - Sample data (sample_input.json)
#
# What is NOT committed:
# - Trained models (.pkl files)
# - Generated predictions (scored_customers.csv)
# - Log files (*.log)
# - Virtual environments (venv/, .venv/)
# - IDE settings (.vscode/, .idea/)
# - OS files (.DS_Store, Thumbs.db)
# - Secrets and credentials (.env, *.key)
#
# To include data files in your repository:
# Comment out the data file patterns above (*.csv, *.xlsx, etc.)
#
# To exclude specific large data files:
# Add them explicitly: data/large_file.csv
